    • Method Detail

      • tryReplaceMatching

        ProgramState tryReplaceMatching(ProgramState toAbstract,
                                HeapConfiguration rhs,
                                Nonterminal lhs)
        If an embedding of rhs in toAbstract can be found it computes it and replaces it with a nonterminal edge labeled with lhs.
        Parameters:
        toAbstract - the target graph
        rhs - the pattern graph
        lhs - the label of the replacing nonterminal edge
        Returns:
        the abstracted graph if an embedding of rhs can be found, null otherwise.

      • prepareHeapForCanonicalization

        ProgramState prepareHeapForCanonicalization(ProgramState toAbstract)
        If the grammar type requires a modification of the graph before it can be abstracted, it is done with this method.
        Parameters:
        toAbstract - the graph which shall be abstracted
        Returns:
        the modified graph (or the graph itself if no modification is necessary)
